Please tell me about oily and acne prone skin products a to z 😢😢😢 and smooth and glass skin

Not sure about the glass skin but as a person who now overcomes acne ( prescribed pills ) , my dermatologist recommended me : cerave normal to oily skin foaming cleanser , frezyderm ac-norm aquatic cream ( moisturizer) , la roche posay anthelios sunscreen ( very important) .
And what you eat is important for your acne , you should eat more fruit and veggies as they help overall with acne and skin wellness, and also hair!

My dermatologist prescribed me accutane, a-derma facewash cause it's soothing when you are on accutane, a-derma moisturiser which helps with acne marks as well, deriva bpo gel which is easily available over the counter too, and no dairy, refined wheat flour or processed foods, she told me to eat an orange everyday, or consume orange juice or any fruit juice if you can't have orange juice everyday. Salads and homemade food should be your go to choice now, it helps a lot.

And if you do not wish to go for accutane, just get ahaglow s facewash or benzac facewash, both are great for oily acne prone skin, another alternative will be saslic. And cosrx snail mucin for hydration
